## Responsive Design

**Mobile-first, always.** Default styles target mobile. Scale up with `md:` and `lg:`.

### Breakpoints
| Token | Width | Use for |
|-------|-------|---------|
| default | < 768px | Mobile ŌĆö design here first |
| `md:` | 768px+ | Tablet ŌĆö expand layout |
| `lg:` | 1024px+ | Desktop ŌĆö full layout |
| `xl:` | 1280px+ | Wide desktop ŌĆö max content width |

### Spacing (Progressive Scaling ŌĆö no big jumps)
| Context | Mobile ŌåÆ md ŌåÆ lg |
|---------|-----------------|
| Page horizontal | `px-4 md:px-8 lg:px-12` |
| Page vertical | `py-6 md:py-8 lg:py-12` |
| Card padding | `p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8` |
| Section gaps | `gap-4 md:gap-6 lg:gap-8` |
| Button groups | `gap-2 md:gap-3` |

**Rule**: `px-4 md:px-8 lg:px-12` Ō£ģ ┬Ę `px-4 lg:px-32` ŌØī

### Touch Targets (mandatory on all interactive elements)
- Buttons and inputs: `h-12 md:h-10` ŌĆö larger on mobile for fat-finger safety
- Icon buttons: `size-12 md:size-10`
- Minimum tap target: 44├Ś44px (never go below this on mobile)

### Typography (Progressive)
| Element | Classes |
|---------|---------|
| Display / Hero | `text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold` |
| H1 | `text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold` |
| H2 | `text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold` |
| H3 | `text-base md:text-lg font-semibold` |
| Body | `text-sm md:text-base` |
| Caption | `text-xs md:text-sm` |
| Amount hero | `text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tabular-nums` |

> **Fluid alternative**: `text-[clamp(1.5rem,4vw,2.25rem)]` scales smoothly between breakpoints without jumps ŌĆö use for splash/onboarding text only; components should use the table above for predictability.

**Note on constrained components** (ModalSheet, ApplePaySheet, bottom drawers): these are always capped at `max-w-md` or `max-w-lg` regardless of viewport. Typography inside them may use a fixed size class (e.g. `text-[25px]` for branded native-style headers) ŌĆö this is acceptable. All other dimensions must still use Tailwind classes, not inline styles.

Content widths: `max-w-prose` (reading), `max-w-4xl` (forms), `max-w-7xl` (dashboard)

### Chat Window Sizing
The chat window must feel native at every size ŌĆö not a shrunken desktop widget on mobile:

```tsx
// Full screen on mobile, floating panel on larger screens
<div className="
  fixed inset-0                          // mobile: full screen
  md:relative md:inset-auto             // tablet+: back to normal flow
  md:w-[400px] lg:w-[440px]             // fixed width on desktop
  h-[100dvh] md:h-[600px] lg:h-[680px] // dvh accounts for mobile browser chrome
">
```

Message bubbles: `max-w-[75%] md:max-w-sm` ŌĆö constrain width to preserve readability.

### Layout Patterns
```tsx
// Side-by-side on desktop, stacked on mobile
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 md:gap-6">

// Grid: 1 col mobile, 2 col tablet, 3 col desktop
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 md:gap-6">

// Hide on mobile, show on desktop
<div className="hidden md:block">

// Show on mobile only
<div className="md:hidden">
```

