## Stories & Figma Make

Every story file must follow this contract so that **props and mock data appear in Figma Make** when a component is cloned.

### `meta.args` ŌĆö required, always

`meta.args` is the single source of truth for Figma Make's props panel. Set it with complete, realistic values covering all required props.

```tsx
const meta = {
  title: 'Primitives/StatusBadge',
  component: StatusBadge,
  tags: ['autodocs'],
  args: { label: 'Confirmed', variant: 'success' },   // ŌåÉ Figma Make reads this
} satisfies Meta<typeof StatusBadge>
```

### `Default` story ŌĆö required, always

Figma Make clones from `Default`. Name it exactly `Default`.

```tsx
export const Default: Story = {}                    // inherits meta.args
export const Default: Story = { args: { ... } }    // add/override if meta.args is partial
```

### Complex props ŌĆö module-scope constants

Array and object props go in named constants at module scope ŌĆö never inline in `args`. This keeps mock data visible in diffs and reusable across variant stories.

```tsx
// Ō£ģ module-scope constant ŌĆö visible in diffs, reusable
const FLIGHTS = [
  { id: '1', destination: 'Tokyo', price: 899 },
  { id: '2', destination: 'Osaka', price: 749 },
]
const meta = { args: { flights: FLIGHTS } }

// ŌØī inline ŌĆö invisible in diffs, cannot be reused
const meta = { args: { flights: [{ id: '1', destination: 'Tokyo', ... }] } }
```

### Compound components ŌĆö expose content via `args`

When a component uses a compound slot API (children as sub-components), the `Default` story must expose key text/content as `args` through a `render` function ŌĆö otherwise the Figma Make props panel is empty.

```tsx
const meta = {
  args: { primaryLabel: 'Book now', secondaryLabel: 'View details' },
}

export const Default: Story = {
  render: (args) => (
    <ActionStrip>
      <ActionStrip.Primary>{args.primaryLabel}</ActionStrip.Primary>
      <ActionStrip.Secondary>{args.secondaryLabel}</ActionStrip.Secondary>
    </ActionStrip>
  ),
}
```

### Story naming convention

| Export | Args | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| `Default` | from `meta.args` | Always present ŌĆö Figma Make's clone target |
| Named variant (`Success`, `Disabled`) | overrides for that variant | One per meaningful state |
| Showcase (`AllVariants`, `AllStates`) | `render: () =>` ok | Visual reference, no interactivity needed |

